Package: SCdetMito
Title: Reference-Aware Adaptive Mitochondrial Quality Control for
        Single-Cell RNA-Seq
Version: 1.4.0
Authors@R: 
    person(
        given = "Silu",
        family = "Hu",
        role = c("aut", "cre"),
        email = "husilu0902@gmail.com"
    )
Description: SCdetMito provides reference-aware and sample-aware adaptive
    mitochondrial quality control for single-cell RNA-seq data. It constructs
    retained-cell profiles across candidate mitochondrial cutoffs, quantifies
    interval-specific cell loss, estimates multiple interpretable cutoff
    candidates, integrates literature-informed reference cutoffs, and supports
    multi-sample QC strategies, benchmarking, sensitivity analysis, cutoff
    confidence reporting, warning generation, and provenance tracking for
    Seurat workflows.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: ggplot2, reshape2, rlang, Seurat
Suggests: DoubletFinder, knitr, rmarkdown, SeuratData, testthat (>=
        3.0.0)
